.Dd May 20, 2026
.Dt MOXY-BATCH 7
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm moxy-batch
.Nd the
.Li batch
meta tool: one approval, many moxin sub-calls
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Xr moxy 1
injects a
.Li batch
meta tool into the unified MCP server.
The tool accepts an array of moxin sub-calls and dispatches them
sequentially under a single outer permission prompt, instead of
demanding one prompt per sub-call.
.Pp
The motivating case is fan-out over a small, known list where the
per-item cost of approval dwarfs the per-item work: delete 25 tags via
.Li grit.tag ,
close a stack of stale PRs, apply a known-good set of edits via
.Li folio.write .
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Bd -literal -offset indent
{
  "calls": [
    {"tool": "<server>.<tool>", "args": { ... }},
    ...
  ],
  "on_error": "stop" | "continue"
}
.Ed
.Pp
.Bl -tag -width "on_error" -compact
.It Li calls
Required.
Non-empty array of sub-calls.
Each entry's
.Li tool
field is a namespaced tool name
.Pq e.g. Li grit.tag ,
.Li folio.glob ;
.Li args
is the sub-call's argument object.
.It Li on_error
Optional.
.Li "stop"
.Pq default
halts the batch on the first sub-call failure and emits
.Li skip
directives for the remainder.
.Li "continue"
runs every sub-call regardless of intermediate failures.
.El
.Sh PERMISSION MODEL
Moxy resolves every sub-call's permission decision through its own
.Li perms-request
machinery
.Pq the same code path the PreToolUse hook uses .
Resolution table:
.Pp
.Bl -tag -width "perms-request" -compact
.It Li always-allow
Sub-call proceeds.
.It Li each-use
Sub-call proceeds without re-prompting
.Pq this is the whole value proposition .
.It Li dynamic
Resolved per call by running the
.Li [dynamic-perms]
script with the sub-call's args; the script's exit code drives the
decision
.Pq Li 0 = allow ,
.Li 1 = ask ,
.Li 2 = deny .
.It Li delegate-to-client
Resolved to
.Em unknown .
.It Li (missing)
Resolved to
.Em unknown .
This covers builtins, child MCP servers, and any tool without an
explicit moxin
.Li perms-request .
.El
.Pp
.Em Any
sub-call resolving to
.Li deny
or
.Li unknown
aborts the entire batch with a single
.Li bailout
record before any sub-call runs.
The
.Em unknown
deny-by-default boundary is intentional: a single mis-typed tool name
or a non-moxin tool reference nukes the batch instead of silently
falling through to per-tool prompts.
.Pp
The
.Li batch
tool itself is annotated
.Li destructiveHint: true
so MCP clients
.Pq Claude Code does
prompt the user once when
.Li batch
is invoked.
That single prompt covers every sub-call inside.
.Sh OUTPUT FORMAT
A single text-block result containing newline-delimited JSON
.Pq NDJSON
mirroring the
.Xr amarbel-llc/tap 7
.Li pkgs/ndjson
schema.
The stream is:
.Bl -bullet -offset indent -compact
.It
Zero or one
.Li bailout
record
.Pq present only on pre-flight rejection or context-cancellation .
.It
Zero or more
.Li test
records, one per sub-call attempted, in input order.
Skipped sub-calls
.Pq Li on_error == "stop"
after a failure
appear with
.Li ok: false
and
.Li directive: {"kind": "skip", "reason": "batch aborted: stopped at #N"} .
.It
Exactly one
.Li summary
record with aggregate counts
.Pq Li passed , failed , skipped , total
plus
.Li bailed
.Pq true on pre-flight rejection or
.Li on_error == "stop"
after a failure
and
.Li valid
.Pq true if execution started, false if pre-flight aborted .
.El
.Pp
The
.Li ToolCallResultV1.isError
flag is true iff
.Li failed > 0
or
.Li bailed .
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Ss Delete 25 upstream tags under one approval
.Bd -literal -offset indent
{
  "calls": [
    {"tool": "grit.tag", "args": {"subcommand": "delete", "name": "v1.13.0"}},
    {"tool": "grit.tag", "args": {"subcommand": "delete", "name": "v1.12.0"}},
    {"tool": "grit.tag", "args": {"subcommand": "delete", "name": "v1.11.0"}}
    /* ... 22 more ... */
  ]
}
.Ed
.Ss Bail out before doing anything when one sub-call would deny
A batch containing a single
.Li slack.send_message
call
.Pq no moxin perm-request
aborts the whole batch with a bailout record;
.Li slack.send_message
is never invoked.
.Ss Keep going past failures
.Bd -literal -offset indent
{
  "on_error": "continue",
  "calls": [
    {"tool": "folio.rm", "args": {"path": "a.tmp"}},
    {"tool": "folio.rm", "args": {"path": "b.tmp"}},
    {"tool": "folio.rm", "args": {"path": "c.tmp"}}
  ]
}
.Ed
A missing
.Pa b.tmp
returns a tool error, the summary records
.Li failed: 1 ,
and
.Pa c.tmp
is still attempted.
.Sh NON-GOALS (v1)
.Bl -bullet -offset indent -compact
.It
Parallel execution.
Sequential only.
.It
Nested batches.
.It
Streaming partial results.
The whole NDJSON document returns in one
.Li ToolCallResultV1 .
.It
Cross-client permission introspection.
.Nm moxy
does not read Claude Code's
.Pa settings.json ;
moxy decides on the basis of moxin
.Li perms-request
only.
.El
.Sh MOXY-SIDE VERIFICATION
The
.Li HandleBatch
dispatch is exercised in
.Pa internal/proxy/batch_test.go
.Pq TestBatch_AllAllow_Sequential ,
.Pq TestBatch_OnErrorStop_DefaultsToStop ,
.Pq TestBatch_OnErrorStop_MultipleSkipsCorrectIndex ,
.Pq TestBatch_OnErrorContinue ,
.Pq TestBatch_PreflightDeny ,
.Pq TestBatch_TransportError ,
.Pq TestBatch_NonTextContent ,
and bats integration tests in
.Pa zz-tests_bats/batch.bats .
The NDJSON record types are defined in
.Pa internal/proxy/batch_ndjson.go .
The permission resolver lives in
.Pa internal/permcheck/ .
.Sh SEE ALSO
